<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-15T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-15T11:00:00-05:00" n="218" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d218">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/3814a:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Deputy Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at
                                Bordeaux</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-15T12:00:00-04:00">June 15,
                                    1940—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>13. President’s communication to Reynaud, No. 1, to Tours date June 13, 1
                            p.m. in which reference was made to numerous utterances of the French
                            and others about continuing the war in Southern France and even across
                            to Africa, and also containing the President’s statements regarding the
                            amount of materials and supplies being furnished the Allies and his
                            assurance of increased quantities from week to week. This dispatch was
                            sent personal and confidential and not to be made public. Please see
                            that this is not done.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>